# Day 23 - Unique Binary Search Trees (Dynamic Programming)

## Problem

**LeetCode 96 - Unique Binary Search Trees**

Given an integer `n`, return the number of structurally unique Binary Search Trees (BSTs) that store values from `1` to `n`.

---

## Approaches Covered

1. Recursion
2. Memoization
3. Tabulation
4. Catalan Number (Mathematical)

---

## Algorithm

Choose every node from `1` to `n` as the root.

For each root:

- Left subtree contains all smaller values.
- Right subtree contains all larger values.

Number of BSTs:

BST(left) × BST(right)

Sum over every possible root.

---

## Complexity

| Approach | Time | Space |
|----------|------|-------|
| Recursion | Exponential | O(n) |
| Memoization | O(n²) | O(n) |
| Tabulation | O(n²) | O(n) |
| Catalan Number | O(n) | O(1) |

